cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a method for training CNN-based object class detectors. It also involves the use of non-maximum suppression (NMS) which is a common technique in object detection. 

The paper also involves the use of mean average precision (mAP) as the training loss, which is a common evaluation metric in computer vision tasks. This suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The paper introduces new gradient-like quantities for piecewise constant functions, which may be of interest to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the PASCAL VOC datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research, suggesting that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
